Ask and you shall receive! I’ve been testing the Revlon Heated Silicone Styling Brush for a couple of weeks now and here are some key points:

1. Amazing for adding loose bends or curls to the ends of your hair and also smoothing the hair out

2. Been loving it for second day hair when my bangs get unshapely or if I’ve lost shape 

3. Gets SUPER hot - my hair felt like garbagé the first time I used it on the hot setting. So be careful.

4. Not sure the silicone bristles will be everyone’s vibe. I’m still trying to figure out if I’m a fan or not. If you have thick hair - it could be an issue.

Have you tried it?! It’s linked in my bio!

Thank you for another insanely busy year 🥹 I don’t post personal life on my page often but between all of the filming, photography, product testing, and editing, here were some snippets of 2022. From watching my baby turn into a toddler, lots of trips/concerts, taking up painting, navigating autoimmune difficulties, and losing sweet little Puffy, there have been ups and downs throughout. After becoming a mom I wondered how I could keep up with the ever growing and changing side of content creation in the beauty space and the answer is because of you all. Some of you from all the way back to 2012 🤯 Somehow this has been my busiest year to date and at times I feel like I’m juggling at a never ending pace but when you have an audience as gentle and kind as mine, it truly keeps me encouraged and inspired to keep going! Thank you to everyone who watches, comments, messages, and supports everything I do! I’m so excited for the endeavors I’ll be embarking on in 2023 and I hope you’ll continue to join me in them ❤️ Happy New Year!
